<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<h2 id="head-cdc124b4bca2cc863418db4dcf65ef8e89e69276">The Robe of Incanus</h2>
<p>
<em>Gandalf's long, flowing robe. It provides insight and allows the wearer to see things not seen by all.</em> 
</p>
<p>
It grants you the power of weigh magic of it is being worn. It can be used to store a spell. It increases your intelligence, wisdom and searching by 3. It sustains your intelligence and wisdom. It provides immunity to paralysis. It provides resistance to acid, electricity, fire and cold. It allows you to see invisible monsters. It cannot be harmed by acid, cold, lightning or fire. 
</p>
<h2 id="head-ff11f0da0a4cd245270f188d8a7299b4084d0328">Chatter</h2>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: I've seen it discussed before on the forum, but I can't find it again and can't remember what it is: What is weigh magic??? <p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: It lists some spell effects affecting the player (blindness, blessing, heroism, etc.) together with the estimated duration. 
</p>
